Package: SurInsulot
Title: Surrogate Indices of Insulin Sensitivity and Secretion
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Zanetta", "Toomata", email = "ztoomata@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A tidy, dependency-light toolkit for computing surrogate
    indices of insulin resistance / sensitivity and insulin deficiency /
    secretion from fasting bloods and the oral glucose tolerance test
    (OGTT). It provides one small, documented, vectorised function per
    index (for example 'homa_ir()', 'quicki()', 'matsuda()', 'igi()',
    'ogis()'), trapezoidal area-under-the-curve helpers, unit
    conversions, and a single 'compute_surrogates()' wrapper that derives
    every estimable index from a data frame. Formulae, units, and primary
    references are documented for each index so the package doubles as a
    reproducible reference for how the measures are defined.
